# Privacy Policy — Block of Ice

**Last Updated:** March 2026  

---

## 1. Introduction
Welcome to **Block of Ice**. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our mobile application.

By installing or using the game, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.

---

## 2. Information We Collect

### a) Automatically Collected Data
We may collect limited technical information to ensure the app functions properly:
- Device type and operating system  
- Application version  
- Anonymous gameplay data (such as score, level progress, and session activity)  

### b) Locally Stored Game Data
The game stores the following data directly on your device:
- Level progression  
- Coins, hearts, and stars  
- In-game preferences and settings  

This data is stored using:
- Local storage  
- Secure native storage (via Capacitor Preferences)  

We do **not** collect personally identifiable information such as your name, email address, or phone number.

---

## 3. How We Use Data
Collected data is used to:
- Maintain and save your game progress  
- Improve gameplay experience  
- Optimize performance and fix bugs  
- Balance difficulty and game mechanics  

---

## 4. Data Sharing
We do **not** sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties.

If third-party tools are integrated in the future (such as analytics or crash reporting), they may collect anonymized technical data strictly for improving the application.

---

## 5. Data Security
- Your data is primarily stored on your device  
- We implement reasonable safeguards to protect information  
- However, no system can be guaranteed 100% secure  

---

## 6. Children's Privacy
Block of Ice does not knowingly collect personal data from children under the age of 13.

If you believe that a child has provided personal data, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

---

## 7. In-App Purchases & Ads
If the game includes advertisements or in-app purchases in the future:
- Third-party providers may collect limited data  
- These providers operate under their own privacy policies  

---

## 8. Your Rights
You have the right to:
- Delete your data by uninstalling the app  
- Reset game progress (if such feature is provided in-game)  

---

## 9. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be reflected with a revised "Last Updated" date.

